 withdraw a medal won through honest hard work on the basis of a challenge, which neither the top coaches nor the top technicians understand, is totally unacceptable!\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"honest hard work\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1206}, {\"ngram\": \"the basis\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"a challenge\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"neither the top coaches\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"the top technicians\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I remember very well how, in communism, the Russians would steal from us at the Olympics, and we'd try to argue with them with no chance of winning.\\\"\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1373, \"end\": 1381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 0.9715468485970712, \"rank\": 0.02928636884316126, \"text\": \"Russians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"communism\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1367}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"no chance\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The turmoil began when Barbosu, celebrating her bronze medal placement, was blindsided by the news her position had been overturned.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The turmoil\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"her bronze medal placement\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1550}, {\"ngram\": \"the news\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"her position\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US gymnastics team made an appeal that Jordan Chiles' routine had been undervalued - and the jury